column8: ##[error]WARNING: Running pip as the 'root' user can result in broken permissions and conflicting behaviour with the system package manager. It is recommended to use a virtual environment instead: https://pip.pypa.io/warnings/venv

column1: ##[group]Run find . -type f -name '*.yaml' -not -name '.readthedocs.yaml' | while read file; do set -ex && grep -q 'LICENSE-2.0' "$file"; done;
